somewhere else and
they are down this path.

00:21:02.027 --> 00:21:04.195
Where are they gonna
go, they are not going
to go to a zoo.

00:21:04.195 --> 00:21:06.265
Zoo's won't take them,
They don't have room for them.

00:21:06.265 --> 00:21:09.901
There are only so many refuges.
It's pretty tight.

00:21:09.901 --> 00:21:12.070
<i> The one wild animal
 I did photograph...</i>

00:21:12.070 --> 00:21:14.639
<i> This is actually
 a real nuisance gator.</i>

00:21:14.639 --> 00:21:16.441
<i> And the guy
 with it is Bob Freer.</i>

00:21:16.441 --> 00:21:18.643
<i> He got his first alligator
 when he was six.</i>

00:21:18.643 --> 00:21:21.179
<i> His dad stopped
 at some roadside place,</i>

00:21:21.179 --> 00:21:22.814
<i> bought him a gator,
threw it in the back, and said,</i>

00:21:22.814 --> 00:21:24.782
"Here you go."
(laughter)

00:21:24.782 --> 00:21:27.619
And so he-- he's spent
his entire life now.

00:21:27.619 --> 00:21:29.720
He's got this place called
Everglades outpost

00:21:29.720 --> 00:21:31.723
and he rehabilitates wildlife.

00:21:31.723 --> 00:21:34.726
