into Miami International Airport

00:21:34.726 --> 00:21:39.830
and he's got, like, snow monkeys
there, and he's got bears.

00:21:39.830 --> 00:21:42.167
But he loves gators
ever since he was a kid,

00:21:42.167 --> 00:21:43.435
and so he wrestles gators.

00:21:43.435 --> 00:21:46.003
He's been an alligator
wrestler for 30 years.

00:21:46.003 --> 00:21:48.840
I asked the man, "What's the
relationship with a gator like?

00:21:48.874 --> 00:21:50.875
What do they want?" He said,
"They want to be left alone."

00:21:50.875 --> 00:21:53.411
(laughter)

00:21:53.411 --> 00:21:54.679
So, you know, I don't know

00:21:54.679 --> 00:21:56.848
what an exotic animal owner
looks like.

00:21:56.881 --> 00:21:58.716
I thought, what if we took
the same animal

00:21:58.716 --> 00:22:02.153
and we did different owners.

00:22:02.153 --> 00:22:06.524
<i> So this is at a thing called
Skunk Fest that was in Ohio too.</i>

00:22:06.524 --> 00:22:07.959
<i> And we photographed,</i>

00:22:07.959 --> 00:22:10.962
<i>you know a little cross section
of some of the owners of skunks.</i>

00:22:10.962 --> 00:22:16.001
<i> This is Travis and
 he's a DJ at a strip club.</i>

00:22:16.001 --> 00:22:19.971
And Nicki is a mother of two.
She's got a skunk.

00:22:19.971 --> 00:22:23.708
<i> And this is Malena. She's 16,
and she dresses up like skunks.</i>

00:22:23.708 --> 00:22:26.310
(laughter)

00:22:26.310 --> 00:22:29.181
<i> And then you've got Maggie,
 she's 12, on the left.</i>

00:22:29.214 --> 00:22:32.617
<i> And Sean's, a technical
 engineer, with his skunk.</i>

00:22:32.617 --> 00:22:36.154
<i> And Cherie's, a housewife
in Pennsylvania, with her skunk.</i>

00:22:36.154 --> 00:22:38.957
<i> But I can tell you honestly
 the bond is true.</i>

00:22:38.957 --> 00:22:41.960
I want to leave you
with something--

00:22:41.960 --> 00:22:44.596
A lot of what these animals
have taught me is patience.

00:22:44.596 --> 00:22:46.798
You need it, 'cause you
can't make an animal do

00:22:46.798 --> 00:22:48.065
what you want it to do.

00:22:48.065 --> 00:22:53.838
<i> So we photographed a hedgehog
 for the cover in December.</i>

00:22:53.838 --> 00:22:56.875
<i> And, you know,
 like the little Gunnison,</i>

00:22:56.875 --> 00:22:58.009
<i> you know,
 I could yell at him.</i>

00:22:58.043 --> 00:22:59.344
<i>When you do that to a hedgehog.</i>

